        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:54AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1154 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gleason, or 9 miles northwest of McKenzie, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sandhill, Ore Springs, Gleason, Osage, Crowley Store, Dresden,
Pillowville, Cottage Grove, Routon, Henry, Como, and McKenzie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
